                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Report by the Deputies</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council adopted the Deputies’ Report submitted by the Chairman in office, and
                    approved the order of the questions referred to it for consideration.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">United Nations Property in Italy</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Compensation for losses sustained</hi> (<gloss
                            target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 177, Appendix III, Part II,
                            2)<note n="33" xml:id="d176fn33">Appendix III of <gloss
                                target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 177 is printed separately
                            as <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 133, June 5, 1946,
                                <ref target="#pg_463">p. 463</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label/>
                    <item>The Council agreed that in principle compensation should be paid for
                        losses sustained, the question of the amount of such compensation to be
                        discussed later.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Settlement of Disputes</hi> (<gloss target="#t_CFMD461"
                            >C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 177, Appendix III, Part II, 3)</item>
                    <pb facs="0549" n="527" xml:id="pg_527"/>
                    <label/>
                    <item>This question was referred back to the Deputies to consider new proposals
                        which would be made to them.</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Italian Property in the Territory of
                        Allied and Associated Powers</hi> (<gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D)
                        (46)</gloss>177, Art. 71)<note n="34" xml:id="d176fn34">For text of the
                        article under reference, see footnote 26, <ref target="#pg_517">p.
                        517</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Council decided in principle that such property could be kept by the nation
                    concerned, the Economic Committee to study the detailed application of this
                    decision, taking into consideration the views expressed by the Ministers.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">IV. <hi rend="italic">Renunciation of Claims</hi> (<gloss
                        target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss>177, Art. 68)<note n="35"
                        xml:id="d176fn35">Article 68 is not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Council adopted the principle of renunciation of claims by the Italian
                    Government, the Deputies to submit a final wording for this clause.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">V. <hi rend="italic">General Economic Clauses</hi> (<gloss
                        target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 177, Appendix IV, Part I)<note
                        n="36" xml:id="d176fn36">Appendix IV of <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D)
                            (46)</gloss> 177 is printed separately as <gloss target="#t_CFMD461"
                            >C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 167, June 12, 1946, <ref target="#pg_488">p.
                            488</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>In paragraph 1 of Part I the Council decided to fix the time limit at eighteen
                    months.</p>
                <p>In paragraph 2 the Council decided to delete the brackets enclosing the word
                    “unconditional”.</p>
                <p>In paragraph 4 the Council agreed in principle to add the phrase proposed by the
                    Soviet Delegation, subject to examination of its wording by the Economic
                    Committee. The U.S. Delegation announced that it would supply the Experts with a
                    draft text on this point.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">VI. <hi rend="italic">Next Meetings</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was agreed that the Deputies would meet at 11 a.m. on Tuesday, 18th June to
                    decide the remaining items on the Council agenda.</p>
                <p>The next Council meeting to be held at 4 p.m. on Tuesday, 18th June.</p>
